name: Artist: Erin Nolan
description: Erin Nolan hails from DeKalb, IL and travels to Door County, WI multiple times a year for much of her inspiration. She is a wood block print artist, creating her art using the accent Japanese tradition of wood block printmaking.  Nolan creates each piece in very limited editions. Her detail and composition is stunning and tends to focus on the natural world.

name: Blue Heron
description:
This regal heron has stunning detail and is one of Nolan's signature works. It has been featured in numerous shows and was on the cover of KNOCK Magazine. This piece is also available framed, please contact the gallery on pricing.

Hand signed and numbered by the artist 13 of 20.

Artwork size approx. 14" x 11"

Experience Art, Finely Crafted

name: Ellison Bay Bluffs
description:
This tree was on a trail that went down the side of a bluff at Ellison Bay Bluff Headlands Park in Door County, Wisconsin.  It shows an abstracted pattern, texture and energy that are Nolan's signature style.

Hand signed and numbered by the artist 2 of 4.

Artwork Size 10" x 11.5"

Experience Art, Finely Crafted

name: Cave Point Park III
description:
The gnarled branches gripping to the bluffs of Cave Point Park in Jacksonport, Wisconsin show the artist that life goes on no matter what the circumstance of our birth. We take root where we are planted and grow to the best of our abilities, forming a rich pattern of growth allowing us to carry on.

Hand signed and numbered by the artist 5 of 10.

Artwork size 8" x 10"

Experience Art, Finely Crafted

name: Large Mouth Bass
description:
As a child the artist would fish with her father and brothers catching bass, bluegill, crappie, etc.  The sun shone brightly as the waves gently rocked the boat, hour after hour.  The fish were cleaned followed by a dinner of fresh fillets. When sleep came that night, she was still being swayed by the water and would dream of the fish. This piece shows the exterior and interior of a largemouth bass as it swims in its blue-green lake.

Hand signed and numbered by the artist, 13 of 24.

Artwork size 11" x 9.5"

Experience Art, Finely Crafted

name: Year of the Rabbit
description:
2011 was the Year of the Rabbit. The Rabbit is well known for its ability to attract good fortune and luck.  This print uses one color, but two blocks of differing amounts of application.

Hand signed and numbered by the artist 4 of 5

Artwork size 12.5" x 11"

Experience Art, Finely Crafted

name: Aurora Borealis
description:
Beautiful ever green in winter with twinkling Aurora in background. Multi-color print with iridescent ink used for Aurora.

Hand signed and numbered by the artist 20 of 24.

Artwork size 5" x 7"

Experience Art, Finely Crafted

name: Ginger Root
description:
The ginger root was purchased at a local grocery store, chosen for its sculptural attributes. It had begun to sprout as it was being drawn. Afterwards, it was planted in the artist's backyard where it flowered the following year.

Hand signed and numbered by the artist 2 of 29.

Artwork Size 12" x 6"

Experience Art, Finely Crafted

name: Hidden Morel
description:
A group of friends walked into the woods treading lightly and looking carefully before taking every step. They walked about twenty feet in before excitedly finding the first morel of Spring. Suddenly, as the group looked down, morels were everywhere! The mushrooms were so well camouflaged in the leaf litter, they had not been detected. These specific morels were located in a secret, undisclosed location in the heart of Door County.

Art Print Size 2.5" x 1.5"

Each print is hand signed by the artists

Hand numbered 14 of 24.

Experience Art, Finely Crafted

name: Honeybee Dance
description: "Honeybee Dance" shows the insects communicating through their figure 8 dance. A bee will dance showing the others where flowers and nectar are located. Based on the original hand carved woodblock, this smaller version was etched into the wood using a laser. This print was hand-lifted by the artist.

name: Squirrel
description:
The artist noticed red squirrels chattering and screeching at her while she began her hike on the paths of the Ridges Sanctuary in Bailey's Harbor, Wisconsin. Not wanting to disturb them, she walked a bit faster thinking that their home was nearby and that she was too close for their comfort. To her  surprise, they followed her – chastising her the entire length of her walk.

Hand signed and number by the artist 10 of 17.

Artwork size 8" x 6"

Experience Art, Finely Crafted

name: Great Horned Owl at the Lagoon
description:
For the past many years, a pair of Great Horned Owls have nested in a wooded patch next to the lagoon at Northern Illinois University in DeKalb, IL. Each year Erin watches the owlets grow from downy, wide-eyed balls of fluff to magnificent, stately adults. This print documents the artist accidently awaking the mother early one morning.

Hand signed and numbered by the artist 2 of 15.

Artwork Size 8" x 10"

Experience Art, Finely Crafted
